<p>Agreed, this whole line of thinking misses a couple very important points:</p>
<p>Firstly, while the site has a broad fanbase, it's not intended to be kid-friendly. The site includes some sexual content and other mature subject matter both serious and farcical. If someone can't deal with that, it probably <em>is</em> best if they leave.</p>
<p>Secondly, exploring concepts considered distasteful or taboo is one of the cornerstones of speculative fiction. It's the genre of &quot;What If&#8230;?&quot;, and asking certain questions can make people uncomfortable&#8230; which is all the more reason to ask them, sometimes.</p>

