<blockquote>
<p>I work it into a draft, few people criticize it, (positively or negatively) I see it as fulfilling all issues brought up, I post it, and after following standard procedure, I get 20 downvotes with no explanation</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Standard spiel regarding posting to the mainsite: no one is <em>required</em> to give you feedback at that point, since authors are expected to have done that before the mainsite post.</p>
<p>Also, I took a look at your post history, and found these:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-2325336/skeletons-in-the-closet:a-sensory-deprivation-scp">http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-2325336/skeletons-in-the-closet:a-sensory-deprivation-scp</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-2234362/hi-returning-after-a-long-time-gone-new-skip-idea">http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-2234362/hi-returning-after-a-long-time-gone-new-skip-idea</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1985619/a-man-who-can-t-seem-to-do-anything-correctly">http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1985619/a-man-who-can-t-seem-to-do-anything-correctly</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1982575/i-can-t-believe-i-found-this-or-that-i-m-posting-it-j-skip">http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1982575/i-can-t-believe-i-found-this-or-that-i-m-posting-it-j-skip</a></li>
</ul>
<p>The -J skip one is from November. In all the threads above, it looks like you didn't always reply, and you only received feedback from one person.</p>
<p>One person is not a good enough representative of the mainsite community. Heck, often 10 or 15 people won't give you a completely reliable prediction of how the site as a whole will vote. Also, you want to try and work on a draft until you know for sure that a couple experienced authors deem it upvote worthy. This means asking for feedback from multiple people, and <em>asking if the changes you made were an improvement, not assuming.</em> The &quot;I see it as fulfilling all issues brought up, I post it&quot; after getting only one or two reviews approach rarely works well on the site.</p>

