<blockquote>
<p>How much of an extension were you thinking here?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I admit, I didn't really have a set timespan in mind, but no longer than a week (which, I suppose, is probably too long to begin with). But like, three-four days, maybe? The idea is that since staff usually write in the discussion pages anyway, they are likely going to see whether the author commits to improving it or not (based on their reply), and could allow for an extension based on that. Ideally, it'd be something that would be negotiated, making it long enough for the author to implement feedback, yet short that it doesn't remain as clutter. However, I realize that staff already have their hands full with everything else on this site, so I'd imagine at least 3-4 days to be fair, or one week at most.</p>
<p>How many new articles get created per day? Do we have any numbers on that?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>How big is your review team, and how often are new pages put up for review attention?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Good question! I can't seem to find our Staff members page (though I fairly sure we have one&#8230;), but according to our Discord chat list, our present Review Team consists of four members. As for how many pages get created, it's hard to say. May had 15, whereas June only saw 2. Though looking over the logs, I'd say we presently see about 10 new pages every month. Most, however, require at least two people to review, and only team members can mark an article as complete.</p>

