														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3165286">
									

<p>I also feel the need to point out, and this is as good a place as any, that an author can ALWAYS repost a previous article, after editing it. Just because it got deleted, doesn't mean you need to give up the idea and move on.</p>
<p>One of the biggest problems we have, and will ALWAYS have, is that this is all VOLUNTEER. So, on top of real, 40 hour at least jobs, schooling, weekend jobs, family life, romance, etc, they also have to put in effort here, for which they get&#8230; nothing. Most of the time, not even thanks. It's why we've had so many people burn out. Hell, I'm still here BECAUSE I have severely limited my interaction with the site&#8230;but I keep at it, because I love this place, and know I will eventually work my way through, well, everything.</p>
<p>Hmmm, Bright works his way through the series&#8230; might have to do that.</p>
<p>But, back on topic: We do what we can with what we have. Generally, I'd advise waiting at least a week on feedback&#8230; or searching it out directly, where possible. And, sometimes, feedback doesn;t get left because it's too much of a mess to bother fixing.</p>

