			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2924415">
									

<p>Do I disagree with some rules? Yes. Do I think they discourage me from contributing? No. My lack of contributions would be me just lurking rather than writing.</p>
<p>My gripes are mostly with forum rules regarding certain usernames and signatures. I'll get onto names in a moment, since the latter issue might be me not understanding or misreading something.</p>
<p>Forum signatures are not allowed? Why? What's the harm in it? Unless it contains something obscene, or is made stupidly long, I don't see any issue with a one-line signature that people aren't even forced to read. Again, I might be wrong regarding it being banned, but I'm going on what I know.</p>
<p>As for names&#8230; I understand why most of it is in place, but there are some things that just gripe me. Usernames with &quot;Class D&quot; in it are banned&#8230; Okay, so I could be banned for a username being &quot;Not-A-Class-D&quot; or &quot;That-Class-D&quot;? Or &quot;O5-J&quot;? I kind of get the third one, but the catchment is too large for my tastes. It just seems like an unnecessary rule - Let people call themselves what they want - If they want D-1234 as a username, I don't see much harm.</p>
<p>Ultimately it's a non-issue and just a pet-peeve of mine, but its related to the site rules, and that is the topic. I just&#8230; don't like it. I feel is discourages creative naming.</p>

