			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3119965">
									

<p>So, something I see a lot is that someone will post an SCP, comment &quot;any help you can give is appreciated&quot;, and get a response of &quot;the mainlist is for finished works, go to the chat and forums if you want help&quot; from some other user. Paraphrasing, ofc.</p>
<p>And I can't find exactly where in the rules that is stated, but assuming that it's out there somewhere: Maybe people should be formally allowed to solicit feedback on posted articles? This wouldn't entail any changes to voting or deletion procedures, nor would it impose any responsibilities on voters or commenters.</p>
<p>It would mostly be a formality, since for all our bluster about this, we do give a lot of feedback on mainsite articles, and there's even a staff team to make sure it happens. New users can easily be forgiven for expecting help with an article they post directly to the site, especially since the chat and forums often leave something to be desired.</p>
<p>Seems like kind of a small thing but it bugs me when new users are having fingers waggled at them about minor bullshit.</p>

