<p>Isn't that just how chat works? It is a bunch of people yelling mostly trivial crap all at the same time. I would advise people who are sensitive to that sort of thing to avoid it. It certainly isn't required to write successfully here, I barely use it.</p>
<p>I would suggest just getting rid of chat entirely, but I gather that is probably a highly unpopular position. I don't think there is any fixing it, other than having more focused channels like #thecritters.</p>
<p>Has anything like that happened here on the wiki proper?</p>
<p>I guess the other question is: should we be more lenient about things like that?</p>
<p>I don't intend to force my views on others, but I also am not going to adjust my voting in order to give racism, misogyny or whatever a &quot;fair&quot; airing.</p>
<p>Personally I would just leave if the tone here shifted back towards a more 4chan like place (and if it got really bad, I would probably delete all my things, Nazis don't get nice things).</p>

