<p>I see what you're saying here, and I've seen the threads in which people explicitly say &quot;You guys are being too sensitive&quot;. That's not quite what we're saying; I know your (staff's) intentions are good.</p>
<p>What OZ and I are trying to get across here is that the current atmosphere is working just fine at keeping immature and otherwise ignorant people from writing about sensitive, easily-misrepresented topics, <em>but is also scaring more skilled writers off like OZ from attempting them at all.</em> The current attitude implies that these sensitive topics should not be touched, <em>period</em>, and woe to anyone who dares try. Or at least it feels that way.</p>

